<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I have made three partitions in an 240GB SSD.</p> <p><strong>partition #1</strong>,600MB for /boot/efi </p> <p><strong>partition #2</strong>,73GB for /</p> <p><strong>partition #3</strong>,150GB for my personal files.</p> <p><strong>partition #1</strong> and <strong>#2</strong> are in fstab ,<em>fstrim.timer</em> will trim it using <em>fstrim.service</em> weekly.</p> <p><code>sudo fstrim --verbose /dev/sda3</code></p> <p>do the above command manually trim <strong>partition# 3</strong>.Since <strong>partition #3</strong> is not in fstab for <em>fstrim.timer</em> to automatically trim it weekly using <em>fstrim.service</em>.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/mysuravnu"> /u/mysuravnu </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/w547w2/is_this_the_correct_way_to_manually_trim_a/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/w547w2/is_this_the_correct_way_to_manually_trim_a/">[comments]</a></span>